RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 1 1M Dirt CR: 70. Claiming Purse 10000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES SINCE DECEMBER 2 OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE MAY 2 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Minnesota Bred Claiming Price $6,250.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: COME ON SWEET PEA saved ground around the first turn, settled off the pace between horses for the run up the backstretch, came around the far turn in the two path, began a bid approaching the quarter pole and kicked clear. PIPER ROSE tracked the leader on the outside through the opening half mile, navigated the far turn from the three path and kept on in the lane. SILVERA raced in the two path early, settled off the pace on the inside for the run up the backstretch, saved ground around the far bend and improved position in the stretch. IMPULSUS raced in the three path around the first turn, continued up the backstretch off the pace on the outside, came around the far turn in the four path and gained ground mildly in the stretch but never truly threatened. ATLANTIC PRINCESS raced in the two path around the first turn, pressed the pace on the outside up the backstretch, dueled from the four path around the second bend and weakened in the final furlong. WORKIN NINETOFIVE saved ground early, led the way on the inside up the backstretch, dueled from the three path around the far turn and tired between horses in the lane.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: HAP HOT angled in and dumped with BLAME J D in the opening furlong, led the way up what remained of the backstretch, saved ground around the bend and drew off in the lane. SEA TO SUCCESS chased the pace setter on the outside through the opening quarter of a mile, came around the turn in the two path and kept on to the finish. BLAME J D was bumped by HAP HOT early on, recovered to stalk that rival on the inside up the backstretch, continued around the turn in the three path and chased on to the wire. HOT SHOT KID raced off the pace on the outside through the opening stages, came around the turn in the four path and was outkicked in the stretch. MONGOLIAN BEE raced off the pace on the inside up the backstretch, navigated the bend from the three path and made no bid. CARMENOOTZ raced in the two path around the first turn, took up sharply entering the backstretch, recovered to chase the leaders from there, began a bid from the three path coming around the second turn, kicked clear entering the stretch and was caught late. FEEDING FRENZY saved ground early, continued up the backstretch off the pace on the inside, navigated the far turn from the two path and improved position late. N. K. KINETIC SWAGGER saved ground around the first bend, dueled on the inside up the backstretch, continued to battle from the rail around the far turn and faded in the lane. TIZONA saved ground around the first turn, raced in the middle pf the pack up the backstretch, came around the far turn in the three path and tired from there.
